const a="Ghatotkacha",e=[{title:"Birth and Heritage",content:"Ghatotkacha was born to Bhima and the Rakshasi Hidimba during the Pandavas’ exile in the forest. Blessed with both Rakshasa powers and Pandava lineage, he grew into a mighty warrior with immense strength and supernatural abilities."},{title:"Early Life and Loyalty",content:"Raised among Rakshasas, Ghatotkacha was deeply loyal to his father Bhima and the Pandavas. Though fierce in appearance, he was gentle and devoted to his family. He often appeared to aid the Pandavas during critical moments."},{title:"Powers and Abilities",content:"As a Rakshasa, Ghatotkacha had extraordinary powers, including flight, illusionary warfare (maya), and supernatural strength. He was most powerful during night battles, where his magical skills made him nearly invincible."},{title:"Role in the Kurukshetra War",content:"Ghatotkacha fought valiantly for the Pandavas, wreaking havoc on the Kaurava army with his illusions and aerial attacks. His presence struck terror among the Kaurava forces, especially during nighttime combat."},{title:"The Great Sacrifice",content:"On the 14th night of the war, Ghatotkacha created massive destruction among the Kauravas. To stop him, Karna was forced to use his divine weapon, the Vasavi Shakti, which he had been saving to kill Arjuna. Though the weapon killed Ghatotkacha, his sacrifice ensured Arjuna’s survival."},{title:"Aftermath and Legacy",content:"Though his death brought grief to the Pandavas, Krishna celebrated his sacrifice, as it turned the tide of the war in their favor. Ghatotkacha is remembered as a brave warrior who gave his life to protect his family and dharma."}],t={name:a,fullBiography:e};export{t as default,e as fullBiography,a as name};
